Introduction

Kassia (카시아) was a South Korean girl group under I-Star Entertainment. They debuted on June 15, 2011 with the digital single Special Girl but were a short-lived group since they disbanded later that year. The group’s name was derived from kasia, which means “bright and pure” in Polish.
